{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866087691,"sessionID":"ses_286223411ffeKbA8FUsl45wcDy","part":{"id":"prt_d79de055d001voyWBZXtPEDxIS","messageID":"msg_d79ddf499001GBWMAR9PYnLiR7","sessionID":"ses_286223411ffeKbA8FUsl45wcDy","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b3213eb8d75e4138829af604","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cli-toolkit/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cli-toolkit/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Pack Command Design\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-020\n4: - **Module**: cmd/cli\n5: - **Language**: Python\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Overview\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Purpose\n12: \n13: The `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Position in Workflow\n16: \n17: ```\n18: ┌─────────┐    ┌─────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌─────────┐\n19: │  pack   │───▶│  build  │───▶│ publish  │───▶│ invoke  │\n20: └─────────┘    └─────────┘    └──────────┘    └─────────┘\n21:      │                                                   │\n22:      └───────────────────▶ status ◀─────────────────────┘\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ### 1.3 Package Structure\n26: \n27: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`\n28: \n29: | Path | Role |\n30: |------|------|\n31: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n32: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n33: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n34: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n35: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n36: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n37: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n38: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n39: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n40: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n41: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n42: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n43: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n44: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n45: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n46: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n47: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n48: \n49: ## 2. Architecture\n50: \n51: ### 2.1 Component Diagram\n52: \n53: ```\n54: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n55: │                        kubectl-agentcube CLI                            │\n56: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n57: │                                                                         │\n58: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n59: │  │                     agentcube.cli.main                          │   │\n60: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐    │   │\n61: │  │  │  Typer app  │  │ pack cmd    │  │ _handle_error       │    │   │\n62: │  │  │             │  │             │  │ version_callback    │    │   │\n63: │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘    │   │\n64: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n65: │                                    │                                    │\n66: │                                    ▼                                    │\n67: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n68: │  │                     agentcube.runtime                           │   │\n69: │  │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │   │\n70: │  │  │                      PackRuntime                         │    │   │\n71: │  │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────┐   │    │   │\n72: │  │  │  │ pack()          │  │ _validate_workspace        │   │    │   │\n73: │  │  │  │                 │  │ _load_or_create_metadata    │   │    │   │\n74: │  │  │  │                 │  │ _apply_option_overrides     │   │    │   │\n75: │  │  │  │                 │  │ _generate_dockerfile        │   │    │   │\n76: │  │  │  │                 │  │ _process_dependencies       │   │    │   │\n77: │  │  │  │                 │  │ _update_pack_metadata       │   │    │   │\n78: │  │  │  │                 │  │ _prepare_output_path       │   │    │   │\n79: │  │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────┘   │    │   │\n80: │  │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │   │\n81: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n82: │                                    │                                    │\n83: │              ┌─────────────────────┼─────────────────────┐              │\n84: │              ▼                     ▼                     ▼              │\n85: │  ┌───────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐  │\n86: │  │ MetadataService   │  │  DockerService   │  │  (future services)  │  │\n87: │  │                   │  │                   │  │                     │  │\n88: │  │ load_metadata()  │  │ build_image()    │  │                     │  │\n89: │  │ save_metadata()  │  │ generate_docker()│  │                     │  │\n90: │  │ validate_workspace│  │                   │  │                     │  │\n91: │  └───────────────────┘  └───────────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘  │\n92: │              │                     │                                    │\n93: │              ▼                     ▼                                    │\n94: │  ┌───────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────┐                           │\n95: │  │ agent_metadata   │  │    Dockerfile     │                           │\n96: │  │     .yaml        │  │                  │                           │\n97: │  └───────────────────┘  └───────────────────┘                           │\n98: │                                                                         │\n99: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ### 2.2 Data Flow\n103: \n104: ```\n105: User Input (CLI options)\n106:          │\n107:          ▼\n108: ┌─────────────────────────┐\n109: │   Typer pack()          │\n110: │   (main.py)             │\n111: └───────────┬─────────────┘\n112:             │\n113:             ▼\n114: ┌─────────────────────────┐\n115: │   PackRuntime.pack()    │\n116: │                         │\n117: │  1. validate_workspace  │\n118: │  2. load_or_create_meta │\n119: │  3. apply_option_over   │\n120: │  4. validate_language   │\n121: │  5. process_dependencies│\n122: │  6. generate_dockerfile │\n123: │  7. prepare_output_path │\n124: │  8. update_pack_metadata│\n125: └───────────┬─────────────┘\n126:             │\n127:             ▼\n128: ┌─────────────────────────┐\n129: │   Return Result         │\n130: │   - agent_name          │\n131: │   - workspace_path      │\n132: │   - metadata_path       │\n133: └─────────────────────────┘\n134: ```\n135: \n136: ## 3. CLI Interface\n137: \n138: ### 3.1 Console Script Entry Point\n139: \n140: ```toml\n141: [project.scripts]\n142: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n143: ```\n144: \n145: ### 3.2 Typer Root Callback\n146: \n147: ```python\n148: def main(\n149:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n150:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n151:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n152:     ),\n153:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n154: ) -> None:\n155:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ### 3.3 Pack Command Definition\n159: \n160: ```python\n161: def pack(\n162:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n163:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n164:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n165:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n166:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n167:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n168:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n169:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n170:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n171: ) -> None:\n172: ```\n173: \n174: ### 3.4 Pack Command Options\n175: \n176: | Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n177: |--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n178: | `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `.` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n179: | `--agent-name` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the agent name |\n180: | `--language` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Programming language (python, java) |\n181: | `--entrypoint` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the entrypoint command |\n182: | `--port` | - | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port to expose in the Dockerfile |\n183: | `--build-mode` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n184: | `--description` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n185: | `--output` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for packaged workspace |\n186: | `--verbose` | - | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n187: \n188: ### 3.5 Helper Functions\n189: \n190: ```python\n191: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None:\n192:     \"\"\"Callback for --version option.\"\"\"\n193:     \n194: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n195:     \"\"\"Handle errors from subcommands.\"\"\"\n196:     # Prints error message in red\n197:     # If verbose, prints full traceback\n198:     # Raises typer.Exit(1)\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ## 4. Runtime Implementation\n202: \n203: ### 4.1 PackRuntime Class\n204: \n205: **Location**: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n206: \n207: ```python\n208: class PackRuntime:\n209:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n210:         self.verbose = verbose\n211:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n212:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n213:     \n214:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n215:         \"\"\"Main entry point for packaging.\"\"\"\n216:         \n217:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n218:         \"\"\"Validate workspace exists and contains required files.\"\"\"\n219:         \n220:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n221:         \"\"\"Load existing metadata or create with defaults.\"\"\"\n222:         \n223:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n224:         \"\"\"Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\"\"\"\n225:         \n226:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n227:         \"\"\"Validate language is supported.\"\"\"\n228:         \n229:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n230:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n231:         \n232:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n233:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n234:         \n235:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n236:         \"\"\"Process dependencies based on language.\"\"\"\n237:         \n238:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n239:         \"\"\"Process Python requirements.txt.\"\"\"\n240:         \n241:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n242:         \"\"\"Validate Java pom.xml.\"\"\"\n243:         \n244:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n245:         \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile if needed.\"\"\"\n246:         \n247:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n248:         \"\"\"Generate Python-specific Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n249:         \n250:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n251:         \"\"\"Generate Java-specific Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n252:         \n253:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n254:         \"\"\"Save final metadata to workspace.\"\"\"\n255:         \n256:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n257:         \"\"\"Prepare output directory.\"\"\"\n258:         \n259:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n260:         \"\"\"Infer entrypoint if not provided.\"\"\"\n261: ```\n262: \n263: ### 4.2 Pack Flow Algorithm\n264: \n265: ```python\n266: def pack(workspace_path: Path, **options) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n267:     # Step 1: Validate workspace structure\n268:     _validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n269:     \n270:     # Step 2: Load or create metadata\n271:     metadata = _load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n272:     \n273:     # Step 3: Apply CLI option overrides\n274:     metadata = _apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n275:     \n276:     # Step 4: Validate language compatibility\n277:     _validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n278:     \n279:     # Step 5: Process dependencies\n280:     _process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n281:     \n282:     # Step 6: Generate Dockerfile\n283:     dockerfile_path = _generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n284:     \n285:     # Step 7: Prepare output path\n286:     output_path = _prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get('output'))\n287:     \n288:     # Step 8: Update and save metadata\n289:     _update_pack_metadata(output_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n290:     \n291:     return {\n292:         'agent_name': metadata.agent_name,\n293:         'workspace_path': str(output_path),\n294:         'metadata_path': f'{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml'\n295:     }\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ## 5. Data Models\n299: \n300: ### 5.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n301: \n302: **Location**: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n303: \n304: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n305: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n306: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n307: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n308: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n309: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n310: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n311: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n312: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n313: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n314: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n315: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n316: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n317: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n318: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n319: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n320: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n321: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n322: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n323: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n324: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n325: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n326: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n327: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n328: \n329: **Validators**:\n330: - `validate_language`: ensures value is in `['python', 'java']` (lowercase)\n331: - `validate_build_mode`: ensures value is in `['local', 'cloud']` (lowercase)\n332: - `validate_port`: ensures value is between 1 and 65535\n333: \n334: ### 5.2 MetadataOptions Dataclass\n335: \n336: **Location**: `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n337: \n338: | Field | Type | Default |\n339: |-------|------|---------|\n340: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n341: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n342: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n343: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n344: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n345: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n346: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n347: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n348: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n349: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n350: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n351: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n352: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n353: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n354: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n355: \n356: ### 5.3 CLI Options to Metadata Mapping\n357: \n358: | CLI Option | Metadata Field | Transformation |\n359: |------------|----------------|----------------|\n360: | `--agent-name` | `agent_name` | Direct assignment |\n361: | `--language` | `language` | Lowercase, validate |\n362: | `--entrypoint` | `entrypoint` | Direct assignment |\n363: | `--port` | `port` | Validate range 1-65535 |\n364: | `--build-mode` | `build_mode` | Lowercase, validate |\n365: | `--description` | `description` | Direct assignment |\n366: | `--output` | (output path) | Used for destination |\n367: \n368: ## 6. Services\n369: \n370: ### 6.1 MetadataService\n371: \n372: **Location**: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n373: \n374: ```python\n375: class MetadataService:\n376:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n377:         self.verbose = verbose\n378:     \n379:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n380:         \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace.\"\"\"\n381:         # Try agent_metadata.yaml first\n382:         # Fallback to agent.yaml, then metadata.yaml\n383:         \n384:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n385:         \"\"\"Save metadata to workspace as agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n386:         # Uses yaml.dump with default_flow_style=False, indent=2\n387:         \n388:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n389:         \"\"\"Update existing metadata with new values.\"\"\"\n390:         \n391:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n392:         \"\"\"Validate workspace has required structure.\"\"\"\n393:         \n394:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n395:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n396:         \n397:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n398:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n399: ```\n400: \n401: ### 6.2 DockerService\n402: \n403: **Location**: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n404: \n405: ```python\n406: class DockerService:\n407:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n408:         self.verbose = verbose\n409:     \n410:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n411:         \"\"\"Check if Docker is available and running.\"\"\"\n412:         \n413:     def build_image(\n414:         self,\n415:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n416:         context_path: Path,\n417:         image_name: str,\n418:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n419:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n420:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n421:         \"\"\"Build Docker image from Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n422:         \n423:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n424:         \"\"\"Get information about a Docker image.\"\"\"\n425:         \n426:     def push_image(\n427:         self,\n428:         image_name: str,\n429:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n430:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n431:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n432:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n433:         \"\"\"Push image to registry.\"\"\"\n434:         \n435:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n436:         \"\"\"Remove a Docker image.\"\"\"\n437: ```\n438: \n439: ### 6.3 Dockerfile Generation\n440: \n441: #### Python Dockerfile Template\n442: \n443: ```dockerfile\n444: FROM python:3.11-slim\n445: \n446: WORKDIR /app\n447: \n448: COPY requirements.txt .\n449: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n450: \n451: COPY . .\n452: \n453: EXPOSE {{port}}\n454: \n455: ENTRYPOINT [{{entrypoint}}]\n456: ```\n457: \n458: #### Java Dockerfile Template\n459: \n460: ```dockerfile\n461: FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS builder\n462: \n463: WORKDIR /build\n464: \n465: COPY pom.xml .\n466: RUN mvn dependency:go-offline -B\n467: \n468: COPY src ./src\n469: RUN mvn package -DskipTests\n470: \n471: FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre\n472: \n473: WORKDIR /app\n474: \n475: COPY --from=builder /build/target/*.jar app.jar\n476: \n477: EXPOSE {{port}}\n478: \n479: ENTRYPOINT [{{entrypoint}}]\n480: ```\n481: \n482: ## 7. Error Handling\n483: \n484: ### 7.1 Error Types\n485: \n486: | Error | Condition | Exit Code |\n487: |-------|-----------|-----------|\n488: | `ValueError` | Invalid workspace path | 1 |\n489: | `ValueError` | Missing required files | 1 |\n490: | `ValueError` | Invalid language/port | 1 |\n491: | `FileNotFoundError` | Metadata file not found | 1 |\n492: | `Exception` | General packaging failure | 1 |\n493: \n494: ### 7.2 Error Handling Flow\n495: \n496: ```python\n497: def pack_command_callback(**options):\n498:     workspace = options.get('workspace', '.')\n499:     verbose = options.get('verbose', False)\n500:     \n501:     try:\n502:         runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n503:         result = runtime.pack(Path(workspace), **options)\n504:         \n505:         # Print success with Rich Progress\n506:         console.print(f\"[green]Successfully packaged agent: {result['agent_name']}[/green]\")\n507:         console.print(f\"Workspace: {result['workspace_path']}\")\n508:         console.print(f\"Metadata: {result['metadata_path']}\")\n509:         \n510:     except Exception as e:\n511:         _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n512: ```\n513: \n514: ### 7.3 _handle_error Implementation\n515: \n516: ```python\n517: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n518:     \"\"\"Handle errors from subcommands.\"\"\"\n519:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n520:     \n521:     if verbose:\n522:         console.print(traceback.format_exc())\n523:     \n524:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n525: ```\n526: \n527: ## 8. Dependencies\n528: \n529: ### 8.1 Python Dependencies\n530: \n531: **Project dependencies** (pyproject.toml):\n532: \n533: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` - CLI framework\n534: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` - Data validation\n535: - `pyyaml>=6.0` - YAML parsing\n536: - `httpx>=0.24.0` - HTTP client\n537: - `docker>=6.0.0` - Docker SDK\n538: - `rich>=13.0.0` - Terminal formatting\n539: - `packaging>=23.0` - Version parsing\n540: - `importlib-resources>=6.0.0` - Resource loading\n541: - `semver>=3.0.0` - Semantic versioning\n542: \n543: **Optional dependencies**:\n544: \n545: - `k8s`: `kubernetes>=28.0.0` - Kubernetes client\n546: - `dev`: `pytest`, `pytest-asyncio`, `pytest-cov`, `ruff`, `mypy`\n547: - `test`: `pytest-mock`, `httpx-mock`\n548: \n549: ### 8.2 Python Version\n550: \n551: ```\n552: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n553: ```\n554: \n555: ## 9. Testing Strategy\n556: \n557: ### 9.1 Unit Tests\n558: \n559: ```python\n560: # test_pack_runtime.py\n561: import pytest\n562: from pathlib import Path\n563: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n564: \n565: class TestPackRuntime:\n566:     def test_validate_workspace_structure_missing(self):\n567:         \"\"\"Test validation fails for missing workspace.\"\"\"\n568:         \n569:     def test_validate_workspace_structure_python(self):\n570:         \"\"\"Test validation passes for valid Python workspace.\"\"\"\n571:         \n572:     def test_validate_workspace_structure_java(self):\n573:         \"\"\"Test validation passes for valid Java workspace.\"\"\"\n574:         \n575:     def test_load_or_create_metadata_new(self):\n576:         \"\"\"Test creating new metadata with defaults.\"\"\"\n577:         \n578:     def test_load_or_create_metadata_existing(self):\n579:         \"\"\"Test loading existing metadata.\"\"\"\n580:         \n581:     def test_apply_option_overrides(self):\n582:         \"\"\"Test CLI option overrides applied to metadata.\"\"\"\n583:         \n584:     def test_generate_python_dockerfile(self):\n585:         \"\"\"Test Python Dockerfile generation.\"\"\"\n586:         \n587:     def test_generate_java_dockerfile(self):\n588:         \"\"\"Test Java Dockerfile generation.\"\"\"\n589:         \n590:     def test_infer_entrypoint_python(self):\n591:         \"\"\"Test Python entrypoint inference.\"\"\"\n592: ```\n593: \n594: ### 9.2 Integration Tests\n595: \n596: ```python\n597: # test_pack_integration.py\n598: class TestPackIntegration:\n599:     def test_pack_python_agent(self):\n600:         \"\"\"End-to-end test for Python agent packaging.\"\"\"\n601:         \n602:     def test_pack_java_agent(self):\n603:         \"\"\"End-to-end test for Java agent packaging.\"\"\"\n604:         \n605:     def test_pack_with_custom_output(self):\n606:         \"\"\"Test packaging with custom output path.\"\"\"\n607: ```\n608: \n609: ### 9.3 Test Fixtures\n610: \n611: ```python\n612: @pytest.fixture\n613: def python_workspace(tmp_path):\n614:     \"\"\"Create a valid Python workspace.\"\"\"\n615:     (tmp_path / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\")\n616:     (tmp_path / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"requests>=2.28\")\n617:     return tmp_path\n618: \n619: @pytest.fixture\n620: def java_workspace(tmp_path):\n621:     \"\"\"Create a valid Java workspace.\"\"\"\n622:     (tmp_path / \"pom.xml\").write_text(\"<?xml version='1.0'...>\")\n623:     return tmp_path\n624: \n625: @pytest.fixture\n626: def pack_runtime():\n627:     \"\"\"Create PackRuntime instance.\"\"\"\n628:     return PackRuntime(verbose=True)\n629: ```\n630: \n631: ## 10. Configuration Precedence\n632: \n633: Configuration is resolved in the following order (later overrides earlier):\n634: \n635: 1. **Default values** (hardcoded in `MetadataOptions`)\n636: 2. **Metadata file** (`agent_metadata.yaml` / `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml`)\n637: 3. **CLI options** (explicit command-line arguments)\n638: \n639: ### 10.1 Metadata File Priority\n640: \n641: ```\n642: 1. agent_metadata.yaml  (preferred)\n643: 2. agent.yaml          (fallback)\n644: 3. metadata.yaml       (fallback)\n645: ```\n646: \n647: ## 11. Usage Examples\n648: \n649: ### 11.1 Basic Pack\n650: \n651: ```bash\n652: # Pack current directory as Python agent\n653: kubectl-agentcube pack\n654: \n655: # Pack specific workspace\n656: kubectl-agentcube pack --workspace /path/to/agent\n657: \n658: # Short flag\n659: kubectl-agentcube pack -f /path/to/agent\n660: ```\n661: \n662: ### 11.2 Pack with Options\n663: \n664: ```bash\n665: # Pack with custom agent name\n666: kubectl-agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent\n667: \n668: # Pack Java agent\n669: kubectl-agentcube pack --language java\n670: \n671: # Pack with custom entrypoint and port\n672: kubectl-agentcube pack --entrypoint \"python app.py\" --port 9000\n673: \n674: # Pack with custom output path\n675: kubectl-agentcube pack --output /tmp/packed-agent\n676: \n677: # Pack with verbose logging\n678: kubectl-agentcube pack --verbose\n679: ```\n680: \n681: ### 11.3 Full Workflow\n682: \n683: ```bash\n684: # Step 1: Pack the agent\n685: kubectl-agentcube pack --workspace ./my-agent --language python\n686: \n687: # Step 2: Build the container image\n688: kubectl-agentcube build --workspace ./my-agent\n689: \n690: # Step 3: Publish to Kubernetes\n691: kubectl-agentcube publish --workspace ./my-agent --provider k8s\n692: \n693: # Step 4: Check status\n694: kubectl-agentcube status --workspace ./my-agent\n695: \n696: # Step 5: Invoke the agent\n697: kubectl-agentcube invoke --workspace ./my-agent --payload '{\"task\": \"hello\"}'\n698: ```\n699: \n700: ## 12. Acceptance Criteria\n701: \n702: | ID | Criterion | Validation |\n703: |----|-----------|------------|\n704: | AC001 | Pack validates workspace structure before processing | Unit test: invalid path raises ValueError |\n705: | AC002 | Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults | Integration test: new workspace gets defaults |\n706: | AC003 | Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata | Unit test: options override metadata fields |\n707: | AC004 | Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java) | Integration test: Dockerfile created |\n708: | AC005 | Pack processes dependencies for the target language | Unit test: requirements.txt validated |\n709: | AC006 | Pack prepares output path and saves metadata | Integration test: metadata saved to output |\n710: | AC007 | Pack displays success output with Rich formatting | Manual test: visual verification |\n711: | AC008 | Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging | Unit test: verbose mode shows traceback |\n712: | AC009 | Pack validates language and port values | Unit test: invalid values raise ValidationError |\n713: | AC010 | Pack infers entrypoint when not provided | Unit test: main.py detected for Python |\n714: \n715: ## 13. References\n716: \n717: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n718: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n719: - Delta spec: `changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md`\n720: - CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n721: - Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n722: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n723: - Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n724: - Python SDK: `python-sdk/design.md`\n725: - client-go library: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 725 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Pack Command Design\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-020\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Overview\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n### 1.2 Position in Workflow\n\n```\n┌─────────┐    ┌─────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌─────────┐\n│  pack   │───▶│  build  │───▶│ publish  │───▶│ invoke  │\n└─────────┘    └─────────┘    └──────────┘    └─────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cli-toolkit/design.md","time":{"start":1775866087671,"end":1775866087687}}}}
