{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866144497,"sessionID":"ses_286223411ffeKbA8FUsl45wcDy","part":{"id":"prt_d79dee2ac001OKA8ACZtz7wVw5","messageID":"msg_d79deda4900129MLbog4QrXosj","sessionID":"ses_286223411ffeKbA8FUsl45wcDy","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_67664d4e4e724613ac3b30ca","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Implementation Tasks\n11: \n12: ### Phase 1: AgentMetadata Model Enhancements\n13: \n14: - [ ] **T001** Review existing `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n15:   - Verify all fields from design are present\n16:   - Confirm validators: `validate_language`, `validate_build_mode`, `validate_port`\n17: \n18: - [ ] **T002** Write unit tests for `AgentMetadata` validators:\n19:   - Test invalid language value raises ValidationError\n20:   - Test invalid build_mode value raises ValidationError\n21:   - Test port out of range (1-65535) raises ValidationError\n22:   - Test language normalization (uppercase to lowercase)\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T003** Run existing tests to verify current implementation:\n25:   - `pytest tests/test_metadata_service.py -v`\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ### Phase 2: MetadataService Load Operations\n30: \n31: - [ ] **T010** Verify existing `load_metadata` fallback chain:\n32:   - `agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n33:   - `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n34:   - `metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n35: \n36: - [ ] **T011** Verify error handling:\n37:   - Test `FileNotFoundError` when no metadata file exists\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T012** Run existing load tests to confirm functionality\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### Phase 3: MetadataService Save Operations\n44: \n45: - [ ] **T020** Update `save_metadata` to match YAML formatting requirements:\n46:   - Add `indent=2` parameter to `yaml.safe_dump`\n47:   - Add `exclude_none=True` to `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T021** Write test for YAML formatting:\n50:   - Verify output uses `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`\n51:   - Verify `None` fields are excluded\n52: \n53: - [ ] **T022** Run save tests to verify formatting\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Phase 4: MetadataService Update Operations\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T030** Implement `update_metadata` method in `MetadataService`:\n60:   ```python\n61:   @staticmethod\n62:   def update_metadata(workspace_path: str | Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n63:       \"\"\"Update existing metadata with new values and re-validate.\"\"\"\n64:   ```\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T031** Implement partial field update logic:\n67:   - Load existing metadata\n68:   - Merge updates into existing metadata\n69:   - Re-validate the updated model\n70:   - Save the updated metadata\n71: \n72: - [ ] **T032** Write unit tests for `update_metadata`:\n73:   - Test partial field update preserves existing fields\n74:   - Test update triggers re-validation (invalid values raise ValidationError)\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ### Phase 5: Workspace Validation\n79: \n80: - [ ] **T040** Implement `_validate_python_workspace` method:\n81:   - Check for `*.py` files in workspace\n82:   - Raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` if none found\n83: \n84: - [ ] **T041** Implement `_validate_java_workspace` method:\n85:   - Check for `pom.xml` in workspace\n86:   - Raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")` if not found\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T042** Implement public `validate_workspace` method that delegates to language-specific validators:\n89:   - Takes `workspace_path` and `metadata: AgentMetadata` as parameters\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T043** Write unit tests for workspace validation:\n92:   - Test valid Python workspace passes\n93:   - Test Python workspace missing .py files raises error\n94:   - Test valid Java workspace passes\n95:   - Test Java workspace missing pom.xml raises error\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ### Phase 6: MetadataOptions from CLI Options\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T050** Review existing `MetadataOptions` dataclass in `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T051** Implement `from_options` class method:\n104:   ```python\n105:   @classmethod\n106:   def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> MetadataOptions:\n107:       \"\"\"Convert CLI options dict to MetadataOptions with defaults.\"\"\"\n108:   ```\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T052** Handle defaults:\n111:   - `language='python'`\n112:   - `port=8080`\n113:   - `build_mode='local'`\n114:   - Empty strings for Optional fields (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, etc.)\n115: \n116: - [ ] **T053** Write unit tests for `MetadataOptions.from_options`:\n117:   - Test full options conversion\n118:   - Test partial options with defaults\n119:   - Test empty strings treated as default values\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ### Phase 7: Integration with Runtimes\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T060** Review existing runtime files:\n126:   - `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n127:   - `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n128:   - `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T061** Verify build metadata integration:\n131:   - Confirm `_update_build_metadata` method exists or needs implementation\n132:   - Store `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n133: \n134: - [ ] **T062** Verify publish metadata integration:\n135:   - Confirm `_update_publish_metadata` method exists or needs implementation\n136:   - Store `session_id` after AgentRuntime CR deployment\n137:   - Store `agent_id` for status checks\n138: \n139: - [ ] **T063** Verify K8s deployment info storage:\n140:   - Store `k8s_deployment` with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ### Phase 8: Provider Integration\n145: \n146: - [ ] **T070** Review `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`:\n147:   - Verify `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` are passed as env vars\n148: \n149: - [ ] **T071** Review `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`:\n150:   - Verify `agent_name`, `port`, `entrypoint` are used in Deployment container config\n151: \n152: - [ ] **T072** Implement `_get_cr_k8s_status` if needed:\n153:   - Extract `agentEndpoint` from CR status\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ### Phase 9: End-to-End Testing\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T080** Run full test suite:\n160:   - `pytest tests/ -v`\n161: \n162: - [ ] **T081** Test pack command end-to-end:\n163:   - Create test workspace with Python files\n164:   - Run pack command\n165:   - Verify metadata saved correctly\n166: \n167: - [ ] **T082** Test metadata validation end-to-end:\n168:   - Create metadata with invalid language\n169:   - Verify ValidationError is raised\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Phase 10: Build & Verify\n174: \n175: - [ ] **T090** Run Python linter:\n176:   - `ruff check agentcube/`\n177: \n178: - [ ] **T091** Run type checker (if configured):\n179:   - `mypy agentcube/`\n180: \n181: - [ ] **T092** Verify all tests pass:\n182:   - `pytest tests/test_metadata_service.py -v`\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## Dependencies\n187: \n188: | Task | Depends On |\n189: |------|------------|\n190: | T001 | None |\n191: | T002 | T001 |\n192: | T003 | T002 |\n193: | T010 | T001 |\n194: | T011 | T010 |\n195: | T012 | T011 |\n196: | T020 | T001 |\n197: | T021 | T020 |\n198: | T022 | T021 |\n199: | T030 | T012, T022 |\n200: | T031 | T030 |\n201: | T032 | T031 |\n202: | T040 | None |\n203: | T041 | None |\n204: | T042 | T040, T041 |\n205: | T043 | T042 |\n206: | T050 | None |\n207: | T051 | T050 |\n208: | T052 | T051 |\n209: | T053 | T052 |\n210: | T060 | All above |\n211: | T061 | T060 |\n212: | T062 | T060 |\n213: | T063 | T060 |\n214: | T070 | T061 |\n215: | T071 | T060 |\n216: | T072 | T071 |\n217: | T080 | All implementation |\n218: | T081 | T080 |\n219: | T082 | T080 |\n220: | T090 | All implementation |\n221: | T091 | T090 |\n222: | T092 | T091 |\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ## References\n227: \n228: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md`\n229: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n230: - Base Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n231: - Existing Model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n232: - Existing Models: `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n233: - Existing Tests: `tests/test_metadata_service.py`\n\n(End of file - total 233 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 Tasks\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: AgentMetadata Model Enhancements\n\n- [ ] **T001** Review existing `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify all fields from design are present\n  - Confirm validators: `validate_language`, `validate_build_mode`, `validate_port`\n\n- [ ] **T002** Write unit tests for `AgentMetadata` validators:\n  - Test invalid language value raises ValidationError\n  - Test invalid build_mode value raises ValidationError","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775866144478,"end":1775866144494}}}}
